cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with motion segmentation in videos. The use of a likelihood function and innovations in initialization suggest that this paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The mention of motion of the observer and complex background geometry suggest that this paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the introduction of a new data set of camouflaged animals suggests that this paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
